 their meat course. Alfyorov bowed for some reason, then went on. “You’re making a big mistake by not taking that as a theme.” (Podtyagin was gently but firmly shaking his head.) “When you meet my wife perhaps you’ll understand what I mean. She’s very fond of poetry, by the way. You two ought to agree. And I’ll tell you another thing—”

Glancing sidelong at Alfyorov, Kolin was stealthily beating time to him. Watching his friend’s finger, Gornotsvetov shook with silent laughte